Conditions in c #28

What is condition?
-- Conditions are way to implement a logical situation in programming. Sometimes we have different situations and based in one situation we have to execute some sort of code rather than other situation.
Ex. If a user logged in our system we want to show their name, otherwise we want to show a login button.
Conditional statement in c programming—

If condition
Else condition
Else if condition
Switch statement condition
__________________________________________________________________
If conditions #29

#include <stdio.h>
int main()
{
if(1){
printf("I will execute\n");
}
return 0;
}

#include <stdio.h>
int main()
{
int condition = 1;
if(condition){
printf("I will get a new bat");
}
return 0;
}

#include <stdio.h>
int main()
{
int a = 21;
int b = 20;
if(a>b){
printf("You are elder\n");
}
return 0;
}
